    "created_at": "2016-08-26T21:18:09Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-08-26T21:18:09Z",
    "body": "> Hmm, yeah, the node integration in Electron is done via calling into node::CreateEnvironment, and the --debug-brk argument seems to be parsed via calling node::Start.\n\nYeah, that's unfortunate. Some of the flags do need to be parsed early, but the others (like this one) could theoretically be handled after `Environment::Start()`. Too bad this isn't how the code works today.\n"
